---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="About AnglerSpecs — free marine rigging calculators for anglers and boat owners.">
  <div class="panel-head">
    <div>
      <h1>About <span class="accent">AnglerSpecs</span></h1>
      <p>Built by an angler tired of doing this math on the back of a tackle box lid.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <article class="guide">
    <p>AnglerSpecs is a free set of calculators for the rigging questions that come up every season: how much trolling motor thrust you actually need, how long a battery will last running LiveScope on the ice, what your prop slip is really telling you, and what the Coast Guard's formula actually says about your transom.</p>
    <p>Every calculator here is built from published spec sheets, manufacturer data, or — where it exists — the actual federal regulation, with the assumptions stated plainly rather than buried. Where a number is an estimate, we say so.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
